# Placeholder so data/trends-blobs/ is tracked in git when JSON blobs are not committed.
#
# A red X on .gitkeep in your IDE is normal — it only means "no blob JSON in repo yet",
# NOT a runtime error. The API serves metrics from the six *.json files when present:
#   daily_ops.json, water.json, hrsg.json, fg_filter.json, air_intake.json, environment.json
#
# Populate locally: copy blobs from Downloads OR run:
#   npm run sync:trends-blobs   (requires AZURE_STORAGE_CONNECTION_STRING)
#
# CI deploy (main_qipp-api.yml) runs the same sync when the GitHub secret is set.
